Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Finland. The Finnish authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus, including recommended self-isolation for 14 days for anyone travelling to Finland from abroad.
On 16 March, the Finnish Government announced that it would make changes to border arrangements. If travelling, please check with your airline or ferry company for the latest position.
Due to the Coronavirus, the Finnish authorities have declared a state of emergency. Finnish borders will be closed initially between 19th March and 13th April to all arriving non-resident foreign nationals with some limited local exemptions. Some flight and ferry connections continue to international destinations, including to London. Check with your operator for further information.
The Finnish Ministry of Health and Social Affairs has opened a Coronavirus hotline (open Monday – Friday, 0800 – 2100 and Saturday, 0900 – 1500) on +358 (0)2 95 535 535. The Finnish Institute for Health and Welfare has up to date information on Coronavirus in Finland.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
You can find more information about cases in Finland on the TravelHealthPro website.
